column5: WTG Bubba despite those water conditions 5 fish is pretty good even if you didn't get the big one .14 days until Wall-ice time.  Were you using floro carbon leaders  .

Nice work Glen!  Bet you didn't forget the plug did ya? LOL.  You did better than I today...I got to go to work, then come home and get ready for hallowe'en.  The fish will have to wait a few more days!
Dawg, those striped bass any good for eating?? (excuse my ignorance if they are awesome...)  Gerritt.
Looks nice and warm! We are about to get some snow up here!
Up here it is a 5 letter word... we add a U to it... SnoUw....like aboUt   thanks for the info about them striped Bass... might have to try and get me a fillet or two  G.

Nice catch glen !!!!!! thats a pretty good day on the water for sure.  ...what were you hittin them strippers on??? they look like they are are a nice size...great pics too.  ..looks warm and sunny there its gonna rain here,so how do you cook up those stripper anyhow????    cheers
Great report G.  Better get those arms worked out for November.  You'll need to for the real sized fish we grow up here  Joey
JEEEEZ I missed this one! Thought I'd better post to it before I get an inbox full of hate mail.  So, Nice report, Glen! Great pics too!
OH ya Roy I know what you mean.
